post.description:
Use this endpoint to search listings using various parameters.As your user provides inputs, you simply pass those inputs to this endpoint to retrieve the listings that match their preferences in real-time.

For more information refer to The Searching, Filtering and Paginating Listings Guide .

Using this endpoint you can also request market statistics, dynamic map clusters and search images using AI.

parameters.name: agent
parameters.description: Filters listings by agent name or agent ID, for example, John Doe. Supports multiple values, for example ?agent=john&agent=mary

parameters.name: aggregates
parameters.description: Aggregates values and counts for specified fields. Aggregates have many use cases, they're particularly useful for grouping and displaying acceptable values for fields that are used in filters. For more information refer to Using Aggregates To Determine Acceptable Values For Filters.

parameters.name: aggregateStatistics
parameters.description: If true, when both "aggregates" and "statistics" parameters are used, the requested statistics will be grouped by the requested aggregates.

parameters.name: amenities
parameters.description: Example usage: ?amenities=Gym&amenities=Swimming Pool

parameters.name: amenitiesOperator
parameters.description: If set to "AND", listings must match all amenities values. If set to "OR", listings must match at least 1 amenities value. Default is "AND"

parameters.name: area
parameters.description: Filter by the geographical area of the listing (also referred to as region)

parameters.name: areaOrCity
parameters.description: Filters listings where either the address.area or address.city field matches any of the provided values.

parameters.name: balcony
parameters.description: Filters listings by one or more values for balcony.

parameters.name: basement
parameters.description: Filters listings by basement description using the supplied value.

parameters.name: boardId
parameters.description: Filter by boardId. This is only required if your account has access to more than one MLS. You may specify one or more board IDs to filter by, if not specified, returns all boards that that account has access to be default.

parameters.name: brokerage
parameters.description: Filter results by brokerage name

parameters.name: city
parameters.description: Filter listing by one or more cities

parameters.name: cityOrDistrict
parameters.description: Filters listings where either address.city or the address.district field matches any of the provided values.

parameters.name: class
parameters.description: The class of listing to filter the search results by. Allowed values: condo, residential, commercial

parameters.name: cluster
parameters.description: If true, enables dynamic map clusters. For more information, refer to the Map Clustering Implementation Guide.

parameters.name: clusterFields
parameters.description: Specifies which listing fields to include in cluster responses. Use comma-separated values (e.g., ?clusterFields=listPrice,soldPrice). For images you can limit quantity with brackets (e.g., ?clusterFields=images[5] returns first 5 images).

parameters.name: clusterLimit
parameters.description: Use this parameter to limit the amount of clusters returned when "map" is specified in aggregates. Values can be between 1 and 200. This parameter can only be used if "map" is specified in aggregates.

parameters.name: clusterPrecision
parameters.description: Use this parameter to adjust the granularity of map clusters. A lower value aggregates listings into less clusters, a higher value aggregates listings into more clusters. Values can be between 0 and 29. This parameter can only be used if "map" is specified in aggregates.

parameters.name: clusterStatistics
parameters.description: If true, when both "cluster" is true and the "statistics" parameter is used, the statistics will be calculated separately for each cluster. This could be useful in scenarios where understanding data on a per-cluster basis is important, such as when analyzing distinct groups or segments within your data.

parameters.name: coverImage
parameters.description: If specified, changes the cover image to the specified feature. For more information, refer to Changing the Cover Image of Property Listings with AI-Powered CoverImage Parameter

parameters.name: den
parameters.description: Filter listings by den description.

parameters.name: displayAddressOnInternet
parameters.description:
If not specified, returns both listings whose address may be displayed on the internet (Y) and whose address should not be displayed on the the internet (N)

Allowed values: Y, N

parameters.name: displayInternetEntireListing
parameters.description: Used to filter listings permitted for display on internet portals. "Y" indicates that the listing can be displayed, "N" indicates that it can not and may only be used for back office purposes.

parameters.name: displayPublic
parameters.description:
If not specified, returns both listings that may be displayed publicly (Y) and those that should be password protected (N)

Allowed values: Y, N

parameters.name: district
parameters.description: Filter by the geographical district of the listing

parameters.name: driveway
parameters.description: Filters listings by one or more values for driveway.

parameters.name: exteriorConstruction
parameters.description: Filters listings by one or more values for exteriorConstruction - note, matches details.exteriorConstruction1 and details.exteriorConstruction2 fields.

parameters.name: fields
parameters.description: Use if you want to limit the response to containing certain fields only. For example: fields?listPrice,soldPrice would limit the response to contain listPrice and soldPrice only. You can also specify the amount of images to return, for example if a listing has 40 images total and you specify fields=images[5] it will only return the first 5 images.

parameters.name: garage
parameters.description: Filter listings by garage description.

parameters.name: hasAgents
parameters.description: If true, only returns listings that have a listing agent assigned to them, if false, only returns listings that do not have a listing agent assigned to them. If not specified, returns both.

parameters.name: hasImages
parameters.description: If not specified, returns both listings that have images (true) and listings that do not have images (false).

parameters.name: heating
parameters.description: Filters listings by one or more values for heating.

parameters.name: lastPriceChangeType
parameters.description: Allows you to find listings that have either increased or decreased in price.

parameters.name: lastStatus
parameters.description:
Filters the last status of the listing. Multiple values may be used, ie: lastStatus=sus&lastStatus=sld&laststatus=exp
Allowed values: Sus, Exp, Sld, Ter, Dft, Lsd, Sc, Sce, Lc, Pc, Ext, New.

For more information on lastStatus meanings refer to lastStatus Definitions

parameters.name: lat
parameters.description: Accepts a value for latitude. Must be used with radius parameter to return listings within a certain radius of a given latitude and longitude.

parameters.name: listDate
parameters.description: Filter listings by a specific date that the listings were added to the MLS. Date format: YYYY-MM-DD

parameters.name: listings
parameters.description: If false, the listings object will be empty. Useful for speeding up responses when statistics and aggregates are requested and listings are not needed. Default is true.

parameters.name: locker
parameters.description: Filters listings by one or more values for locker.

parameters.name: long
parameters.description: Accepts a value for longitude. Must be used with radius parameter to return listings within a certain radius of a given latitude and longitude.

parameters.name: mapOperator
parameters.description: When a multi-polygon is provided for the "map" parameter the default condition is "OR", meaning that it will return all listings that fall inside any of the polygons. This can be changed to "AND" in which case it will return listings that fall inside all of the polygons.

parameters.name: maxBedrooms
parameters.description: Filters properties based on the number of bedrooms that were part of the original floorplan, typically located above grade.

parameters.name: maxBedroomsPlus
parameters.description: Filters properties based on the number of additional bedrooms added beyond the original floorplan. These bedrooms can be located in areas like basements or attics and were not part of the initial construction.

parameters.name: maxBedroomsTotal
parameters.description: Filters properties by the total number of bedrooms, combining both numBedrooms and numBedroomsPlus. This provides a comprehensive look at all spaces being used as bedrooms.

parameters.name: maxListDate
parameters.description: Filter listings that were listed on or before the supplied value. Date format: YYYY-MM-DD

parameters.name: maxLotSizeSqft
parameters.description: Filter lot size by maximum square feet.

parameters.name: maxMaintenanceFee
parameters.description: If supplied, filters listings whose maintenance fee is <= the supplied value.

parameters.name: maxOpenHouseDate
parameters.description: If specified, filters listings that have an open house on or before the supplied date. Date format: YYYY-MM-DD

parameters.name: maxPriceChangeDateTime
parameters.description: Filters listings that have had a price change on or before the date specified.

parameters.name: maxRepliersUpdatedOn
parameters.description: Filters listings whose repliersUpdatedOn is the same or less than the supplied DateTime. repliersUpdatedOn is an internal timestamp, this may be useful for polling applications to identify listings that have updates in information that's exclusive of MLS updates. For example, if an estimate is recalculated since the estimate is not provided by the MLS.

parameters.name: maxSoldDate
parameters.description: Filter listings that were sold/leased on or before the supplied value. Date format: YYYY-MM-DD

parameters.name: maxSoldPrice
parameters.description: Filter listings whose sold price is <= the supplied value.

parameters.name: maxStreetNumber
parameters.description: This parameter enables users to filter results by specifying the maximum street number. It ensures that the street number of the listing is less than or equal to the value provided. This is helpful when users are interested in properties within a specific range of street numbers, excluding listings that fall outside this range.

parameters.name: maxSqft
parameters.description: Filter listings whose square footage is <= the supplied value. Note - excludes listings where the sqft value is not supplied by the MLS.

parameters.name: maxTaxes
parameters.description: Filters listings whose annual tax amount is equal to or less than the supplied value.

parameters.name: maxUnavailableDate
parameters.description: Filter listings that became unavailable on or before the supplied value. Not all MLSes support this parameter.

parameters.name: maxUpdatedOn
parameters.description: Filter listings that were updated on or before the supplied value.

parameters.name: maxYearBuilt
parameters.description: Filter listings whose year built value is <= the supplied value. excludes listings where the year built value is not supplied by the MLS.

parameters.name: minBedrooms
parameters.description: Filters properties based on the number of bedrooms that were part of the original floorplan, typically located above grade.

parameters.name: minBedroomsPlus
parameters.description: Filters properties based on the number of additional bedrooms added beyond the original floorplan. These bedrooms can be located in areas like basements or attics and were not part of the initial construction.

parameters.name: minBedroomsTotal
parameters.description: Filters properties by the total number of bedrooms, combining both numBedrooms and numBedroomsPlus. This provides a comprehensive look at all spaces being used as bedrooms.

parameters.name: minGarageSpaces
parameters.description: Filters listings that have >= the supplied value of garage spaces.

parameters.name: minListDate
parameters.description: Filter listings that were listed on or after the supplied value. Date format: YYYY-MM-DD

parameters.name: minLotSizeSqft
parameters.description: Filter lot size by minimum square feet.

parameters.name: minOpenHouseDate
parameters.description: If specified, filters listings that have an open house on or after the supplied date. Date format: YYYY-MM-DD

parameters.name: minPriceChangeDateTime
parameters.description: Filters listings that have had a price change on or after the date specified.

parameters.name: minRepliersUpdatedOn
parameters.description: Filters listings whose repliersUpdatedOn is the same or greater than the supplied DateTime. repliersUpdatedOn is an internal timestamp, this may be useful for polling applications to identify listings that have updates in information that's exclusive of MLS updates. For example, if an estimate is recalculated since the estimate is not provided by the MLS.

parameters.name: minSoldDate
parameters.description: Filter listings that were sold/leased on or after the supplied value. Date format: YYYY-MM-DD

parameters.name: minSoldPrice
parameters.description: Filter listings whose sold price is >= the supplied value.

parameters.name: minSqft
parameters.description: Filter listings whose square footage is >= the supplied value. Note - excludes listings where the sqft value is not supplied by the MLS.

parameters.name: minStreetNumber
parameters.description: This parameter allows users to filter results by specifying the minimum street number. It ensures that the street number of the listing is greater than or equal to the value provided. This is particularly useful for narrowing down search results to properties within a specific range of street numbers.

parameters.name: minTaxes
parameters.description: Filters listings whose annual tax amount is equal to or greater than the supplied value.

parameters.name: minUnavailableDate
parameters.description: Filter listings that became unavailable on or after the supplied value. Not all MLSes support this parameter. Date format: YYYY-MM-DD

parameters.name: minUpdatedOn
parameters.description: Filter listings that were updated on or after the supplied value.

parameters.name: minYearBuilt
parameters.description: Filter listings whose year built value is >= the supplied value. excludes listings where the year built value is not supplied by the MLS.

parameters.name: mlsNumber
parameters.description: Filter listings by one or more MLS numbers.

parameters.name: neighborhood
parameters.description: Filter by the geographical neighborhood that the listing is situated in. For example GET /listings?city=Vaughan&neighborhood=Sonoma Heights&neighborhood=Vellore Village

parameters.name: officeId
parameters.description: Filter listings by the office ID of the listing brokerage.

parameters.name: operator
parameters.description: If set to "AND", listings must match all supplied parameters. If set to "OR", listings must match at least 1 parameter. Default is "AND"

parameters.name: pageNum
parameters.description: If specified indexes a specific page in the results set. For example, if there are 1000 listings and 100 listings per page, if you'd like to view listings 101-201 you'd specify pageNum=2

parameters.name: propertyType
parameters.description: Filters listings by one or more property types.

parameters.name: propertyTypeOrStyle
parameters.description: Filters listings where either details.propertyType or the details.style field matches any of the provided values.

parameters.name: radius
parameters.description: Accepts a value for radius in KM. Must be used with lat and long parameters to return listings within a certain radius of a given latitude and longitude.

parameters.name: resultsPerPage
parameters.description: The amount of listings to return in each page of the results set.

parameters.name: search
parameters.description: One or more keywords may be specified to filter the results by. For more information refer to Full-Text Keyword Search Implementation Guide.

parameters.name: searchFields
parameters.description: To be used in conjunction with the "search" parameter. If specified, limits the keyword search to specific fields. For example, if search=yonge and you want to limit the search to streetName you would specify searchFields=address.streetName

parameters.name: sortBy
parameters.description: The attribute that the listings will be sorted by. Note, distanceAsc and distanceDesc must be used in combination with lat, long and radius parameters. Default is updatedOnDesc

parameters.name: sqft
parameters.description: Filters listings by one or more values for sqft.

parameters.name: statistics
parameters.description: Use this parameter to request statistics relevant to the listings returned in your search. For more information, refer to the Real-Time Market Statistics Implementation Guide

parameters.name: standardStatus
parameters.description: Use this parameter to filter by Standard Status.

parameters.name: status
parameters.description: Set status=A to retrieve active listings. Set status=U to retrieve unavailable listings. Set status=A&status=U to retrieve both active and unavailable listings.

parameters.name: streetDirection
parameters.description: Filter listings by one or more street directions

parameters.name: streetName
parameters.description: Filter by the street name of the listing (excluding the street suffix and direction, for example "Yonge")

parameters.name: streetNumber
parameters.description: Filter by the street number of the listing.

parameters.name: streetSuffix
parameters.description: Filter listings by one or more street suffixes

parameters.name: style
parameters.description: Filter by the property style of the listing.

parameters.name: swimmingPool
parameters.description: Filter listings by one of more values for swimmingPool.

parameters.name: type
parameters.description:
Used to filter properties that are for sale or for lease. If not specified, will return listings of all types.

Allowed values:

sale, lease

parameters.name: unitNumber
parameters.description: Filter by one or more unit numbers.

parameters.name: updatedOn
parameters.description: Filter listings by a specific date that the listings were last updated on the MLS. Date format: YYYY-MM-DD

parameters.name: waterSource
parameters.description: Filter listings by one or more values for waterSource.

parameters.name: repliersUpdatedOn
parameters.description: Filters listings whose repliersUpdatedOn is a specific date. repliersUpdatedOn is an internal timestamp, this may be useful for polling applications to identify listings that have updates in information that's exclusive of MLS updates. For example, if an estimate is recalculated since the estimate is not provided by the MLS.

parameters.name: sewer
parameters.description: Filters listings by one or more values for sewer.

parameters.name: state
parameters.description: Filter by the address state of the listing, for example "NY"

parameters.name: waterfront
parameters.description: If not specified, returns both listings that are waterfront and those that are not. If "Y", returns listings that are waterfront, if "N" returns listings that are not waterfront or unspecified.

parameters.name: yearBuilt
parameters.description: Filter listings by one or more values for yearBuilt.

parameters.name: zip
parameters.description: Filters listings by postal or zip code.

parameters.name: zoning
parameters.description: Filter listings by zoning description.

imageSearchItems.description: An array of objects used with our AI Image Search feature. For more information refer to our AI Image Search Implementation Guide.

type.description: Indicates if the imageSearchItem is an image input or a text input.

url.description: The url of the image. To be used if type=Image

value.description: The value of the text. To be used if type=Text. Example: White Kitchen

boost.description: A value indicating the importance of the imageSearchItem. The greater the value, the more important it is in comparison with other imageSearchItems. May be used when multiple imageSearchItems are provided in a single request.

get.description:
Provide this endpoint with an mls number and it'll retrieve similar properties that are also for sale.

This is really useful if you'd like to show your users other properties they may be interested in.

By default this endpoint will retrieve similar properties in the same neighborhood, however you can override this by using a radius parameter.

parameters.name: mlsNumber
parameters.description: The MLS number of the listing you wish to retrieve similar listings for.

parameters.name: boardId
parameters.description: Filter by boardId. This is only required if your account has access to more than one MLS. You may specify one or more board IDs to filter by, if not specified, returns all boards that that account has access to be default.

parameters.name: fields
parameters.description: Use if you want to limit the response to containing certain fields only. For example: fields?listPrice,soldPrice would limit the response to contain listPrice and soldPrice only. You can also specify the amount of images to return, for example if a listing has 40 images total and you specify fields=images[5] it will only return the first 5 images.

parameters.name: listPriceRange
parameters.description: If specified, returns similar listings whose listPrice are +/- the supplied value, for a given listing. For example, if the given listing is 1M and listPriceRange is 250k, similar listings between 750k and 1.25M will be returned.

parameters.name: radius
parameters.description: If specified, will show similar listings within the specified radius (km). If not specified, defaults to showing listings in the same neighborhood.

parameters.name: sortBy
parameters.description:
Allowed values:

updatedOnDesc,updatedOnAsc,createdOnAsc,createdOnDesc

get.description:
Use this endpoint to retrieve the MLS history of a specific address.

In addition to displaying the history you could also use the information in the response to create a graph that illustrates the change in value over time.

parameters.name: city
parameters.description: The city of the property. Note - a city is not required if a zip is provided.

parameters.name: zip
parameters.description: The zip code or postal code of the property. Supports partial match, for example if supplied value is "123" it will match "12345".  Note - a zip is not required if a city is provided.

get.description: Use this endpoint to retrieve listings that have been deleted from the MLS. Listings that have been deleted from the MLS should not be displayed in your websites and apps. Note - deleted listings are not applicable in some MLSes.
Use this endpoint to list geographical location data such as areas, cities and neighborhoods.

parameters.name: area
parameters.description: Limits location metadata to areas, cities and neighborhoods whose area matches the supplied valued.

parameters.name: city
parameters.description: Limits location metadata to areas, cities and neighborhoods whose city matches the supplied valued.

parameters.name: class
parameters.description: Limits location metadata to areas, cities and neighborhoods whose class matches the supplied valued.

parameters.name: neighborhood
parameters.description: Limits location metadata to areas, cities and neighborhoods whose neighborhood matches the supplied valued.

parameters.name: search
parameters.description: If a value is supplied, limits location meta data to areas, cities or neighborhoods that match or partially match the supplied value.

get.description: Search locations based on the provided filter criteria

parameters.name: type
parameters.description:
Limits results to specified location types:
- area: Represents larger geographical divisions that may contain multiple cities and neighborhoods. Examples of Areas are counties, regions etc.
- city: Municipal division that can include multiple neighborhoods within its boundaries.
- neighborhood: Smallest geographical unit within a city.

parameters.name: area
parameters.description:
Filters locations by area names. Returns locations within the specified area.
Areas represent larger geographical divisions that may contain multiple cities and neighborhoods. Examples of Areas are counties, regions etc.

parameters.name: city
parameters.description:
Filters locations by city names. Returns locations within the specified city.
Cities can include multiple neighborhoods within their boundaries.

parameters.name: neighborhood
parameters.description:
Filter results by neighborhood names. Returns specified neighborhoods.
Neighborhoods represent the smallest geographical division in the hierarchy.

parameters.name: locationId
parameters.description: Filters by location IDs. Location IDs can be obtained from response of [Locations Autocomplete](/locations/autocomplete) endpoint

parameters.name: fields
parameters.description:
Comma-separated list of fields to include in the response.
This allows clients to request only the specific data they need, reducing payload size.
Examples:
- `name,type` - Returns only location names and types
- `name,address.city,address.state` - Returns location names and specific address components
- `map.boundary` - Returns only geographical boundary data

parameters.name: resultsPerPage
parameters.description: The amount of locations to return in each page of the results set.

parameters.name: pageNum
parameters.description: If specified indexes a specific page in the results set. For example, if there are 1000 locations and 100 locations per page, if you'd like to view locations 101-200 you'd specify pageNum=2

parameters.name: map
parameters.description:
GeoJSON polygon or multi-polygon boundary for geographical filtering. Limits results to locations within the specified boundaries.
For complex polygons or multipolygons that exceed query parameter size limits, use the POST method
and include the map data in the request body.

Format: Array of coordinate arrays, where each coordinate is [longitude, latitude] in WGS 84 format.
The polygon must be closed (first and last points must be identical).

For more information refer to the implementation guide  [Filtering Listings Geo-Spatially Using the "map" Parameter](https://help.repliers.com/en/article/filtering-listings-geo-spatially-using-the-map-parameter-7sorw0/)

parameters.name: radius
parameters.description: Accepts a value for radius in KM. Must be used with `lat` and `long` parameters to return locations within the specified radius of a given latitude and longitude.

parameters.name: lat
parameters.description: Accepts a value for latitude. Must be used with radius parameter to return listings within a certain radius of a given latitude and longitude.

parameters.name: long
parameters.description: Accepts a value for longitude. Must be used with radius parameter to return listings within a certain radius of a given latitude and longitude.

parameters.name: sortBy
parameters.description: Sort results by type

items.description:
Complete location information including identifiers, type classification,
address components, and geographical coordinates/boundaries.

name.description: Human-readable display name for the location

type.description:
Hierarchical classification of the location:
- area: Represent larger geographical divisions that may contain multiple cities and neighborhoods. Examples of Areas are counties, regions etc.
- city: Municipal division that can include multiple neighborhoods within its boundaries.
- neighborhood: Smallest geographical unit within a city

map.description: Geographical information including coordinates and boundary data

latitude.description: Latitude coordinate of the location's center point

longitude.description: Longitude coordinate of the location's center point

point.description: WKT (Well-Known Text) representation of the location's center point

boundary.description: GeoJSON polygon defining the location's geographical boundary.

address.description: Structured representation of a location's address components.

get.description: Autocomplete for Locations search. As your user types, you simply pass their input into search param and get locations which match their input. You can use other params to fine-tune the locations which will be returned for a given search.

parameters.name: search
parameters.description: Search query string

parameters.name: type
parameters.description:
Limits results to specified location types:
- area: Represents larger geographical divisions that may contain multiple cities and neighborhoods. Examples of Areas are counties, regions etc.
- city: Municipal division that can include multiple neighborhoods within its boundaries.
- neighborhood: Smallest geographical unit within a city.

parameters.name: fields
parameters.description:
Comma-separated list of fields to include in the response.
This allows clients to request only the specific data they need, reducing payload size.
Examples:
- `name,type` - Returns only location names and types
- `name,address.city,address.state` - Returns location names and specific address components
- `map.boundary` - Returns only geographical boundary data

parameters.name: map
parameters.description:
GeoJSON polygon or multi-polygon boundary for geographical filtering. Limits results to locations within the specified boundaries.
For complex polygons or multipolygons that exceed query parameter size limits, use the POST method
and include the map data in the request body.

Format: Array of coordinate arrays, where each coordinate is [longitude, latitude] in WGS 84 format.
The polygon must be closed (first and last points must be identical).

For more information refer to the implementation guide  [Filtering Listings Geo-Spatially Using the "map" Parameter](https://help.repliers.com/en/article/filtering-listings-geo-spatially-using-the-map-parameter-7sorw0/)

parameters.name: resultsPerPage
parameters.description: The amount of locations to return in each page of the results set.

parameters.name: radius
parameters.description: Accepts a value for radius in KM. Must be used with `lat` and `long` parameters to return locations within the specified radius of a given latitude and longitude.

parameters.name: lat
parameters.description: Accepts a value for latitude. Must be used with radius parameter to return listings within a certain radius of a given latitude and longitude.

parameters.name: long
parameters.description: Accepts a value for longitude. Must be used with radius parameter to return listings within a certain radius of a given latitude and longitude.

parameters.name: area
parameters.description:
Searches for locations only inside specified areas.
Areas represent larger geographical divisions that may contain multiple cities and neighborhoods. Examples of Areas are counties, regions etc.

parameters.name: city
parameters.description:
Searches for locations only inside specified cities.
Cities can include multiple neighborhoods within their boundaries.

parameters.name: boundary
parameters.description: Fetches locations with boundary polygons for a small performance penalty of 10-20ms

name.description: Human-readable display name for the location

items.description:
A longitude/latitude coordinate pair in WGS 84 format.
Format: [longitude, latitude] where:
- Longitude ranges from -180 to +180 degrees (negative for western hemisphere)
- Latitude ranges from -90 to +90 degrees (negative for southern hemisphere)

get.description: Use this endpoint to list brokerages belonging to the MLS.
Use this endpoint to list offices belonging to the MLS. A brokerage may have one or more offices.

parameters.name: keywords
parameters.description: If supplied, filters offices by the supplied value.

parameters.name: boardId
parameters.description: Find your boardId by visiting https://login.repliers.com/dashboard/data-access

get.description: Use this endpoint to list members (agents) belonging to the MLS.

parameters.name: keywords
parameters.description: If supplied, filters offices by the supplied value.

parameters.name: pageNum
parameters.description: If specified loads a specific page in the results set. For example, if there are 1000 buildings and 100 buildings per page, if you'd like to view buildings 101-201 you'd specify pageNum=2

parameters.name: resultsPerPage
parameters.description: The amount of buildings to return in each page of the results set.

parameters.name: city
parameters.description: Filters buildings by one or more cities

parameters.name: neighborhood
parameters.description: Filter by one more geographical neighborhoods that the building is situated in. For example GET /listings/buildings?city=Vaughan&neighborhood=Sonoma Heights&neighborhood=Vellore Village

parameters.name: class
parameters.description: The class of listing to filter the search results by. Allowed values: condo, residential, commercial

parameters.name: propertyType
parameters.description: Filters buildings by one or more property types.

parameters.name: type
parameters.description: Used to filter properties that are for sale or for lease. If not specified, will return listings of all types. Allowed values: Sale, Lease

parameters.name: streetName
parameters.description: Filter by the street name of the building (excluding the street suffix and direction, for example "Yonge")

parameters.name: streetNumber
parameters.description: Filter by the street number of the building.

parameters.name: sortBy
parameters.description:
The attribute that the buildings will be sorted by.

Allowed values:

numUnitsDesc

parameters.name: displayPublic
parameters.description: If not specified, returns both listings that may be displayed publicly (Y) and those that should be password protected (N) Allowed values: Y, N

get.description: Use this endpoint to retrieve relevant schools, parks, transit stops and safety places for a given latitude and longitude. This endpoint is useful to enrich property and neighborhood views with local places information.

parameters.name: lat
parameters.description: The latitude of the point that you'd like to retrieve places data for.

parameters.name: long
parameters.description: The longitude of the point that you'd like to retrieve places data for.

post.description: Use this endpoint to create an agent. Each client that you create needs to be associated with an agent, therefore it's necessary to create at least one agent before you start creating clients.

fname.description: The first name of the agent.

lname.description: The last name of the agent.

phone.description:
The mobile phone number of the agent. Must be 11 digits in length.

Regex pattern: ^(1)([0-9]{10})$

brokerage.description: The name of the Brokerage/Office that this agent is registered with.

designation.description: This agent's designation. For example, "Sales Representative"

avatar.description: A URL/Path to an avatar/picture of this agent.

status.description: If false, disables all operations for the agent.

latitude.description: A latitude value representing the location of the agent. Required if a value for longitude is provided.

longitude.description: A longitude value representing the location of the agent. Required if a value for latitude is specified.

externalId.description: The externalId is intended for storing agent identifiers from external systems (such as CRMs) for reference purposes.

get.description: Use this endpoint to get a list of agents that you've created. You can filter for specific agents using parameters like email address and first name. If you don't use any filters all agents will be returned.

parameters.name: externalId
parameters.description: Filter agents by their identifier from an external system (such as a CRM).

patch.description: Use this endpoint to update information associated with an agent.

fname.description: The first name of the agent.

lname.description: The last name of the agent.

phone.description:
The mobile phone number of the agent. Must be 11 digits in length.

Regex pattern: ^(1)([0-9]{10})$

brokerage.description: The name of the Brokerage/Office that this agent is registered with.

designation.description: This agent's designation. For example, "Sales Representative"

avatar.description: A URL/Path to an avatar/picture of this agent.

status.description: If false, disables all operations for the agent.

latitude.description: A latitude value representing the location of the agent. Required if a value for longitude is provided.

longitude.description: A longitude value representing the location of the agent. Required if a value for latitude is specified.

externalId.description: The externalId is intended for storing agent identifiers from external systems (such as CRMs) for reference purposes.

delete.description: Use this endpoint to delete an agent. You must specify a new agentId to assign the deleted agent's clients to.

get.description: Use this endpoint to lookup details about a specific agent.

post.description: Use this endpoint to transfer all clients from one agent to another.

parameters.name: agentId
parameters.description: The agentId of the agent whose clients will be transferred to another agent.

newAgentId.description: The agentId of the new agent who will takeover clients from the previous agent.

post.description: Use this endpoint to create a client. When creating saved searches, messages or favorites a client needs to be specified.

agentId.description: The agentId of the agent that this client is assigned to. Each client must be assigned to an agent.

fname.description: The first name of this client

lname.description: The last name of this client.

phone.description:
The mobile phone number of this client (May be used to deliver text messages). Must be 11 digits in length.

Regex pattern: ^(1)([0-9]{10})$

status.description: If false, disables all operations for the client.

email.description: If false, the client will not receive messages via email

sms.description: If false, the client will not receive messages via sms (text)

unsubscribe.description: If true, unsubscribes the client from all forms of communication.

tags.description: You may categorize this client using tags. Tags are useful for filtering purposes and building lists of specific clients. For example, if this client is a buyer from Toronto, you may want to create tags for "Buyer" and "Toronto".

externalId.description: The externalId is intended for storing client identifiers from external systems (such as CRMs) for reference purposes.

get.description: Use this endpoint to get a list of clients that you've created. You can filter for specific clients using parameters like email address and first name. If you don't use any filters all clients will be returned.

parameters.name: keywords
parameters.description: One or more keywords may be specified to filter the results by. Useful for searching clients. If specified all other params are ignored.

parameters.name: condition
parameters.description:
Determines the search condition applied to the filters. If EXACT, requires that the given value for one or more params is an exact match of the stored value. If CONTAINS, requires that the given value for one or more params is contained within the stored value.

Allowed values:

EXACT, CONTAINS

parameters.name: operator
parameters.description:
Determines the search logic applied to the filters. If OR, requires that one or more params contain/equal the given value. If AND, requires that all params contain/equal the given value.

Allowed values:

OR, AND

parameters.name: pageNum
parameters.description: If specified indexes a specific page in the results set. For example, if there are 1000 listings and 100 listings per page, if you'd like to view listings 101-201 you'd specify pageNum=2

parameters.name: resultsPerPage
parameters.description: The amount of listings to return in each page of the results set.

parameters.name: tags
parameters.description: One or more comma separated strings that can be used to filter clients.  For example GET /clients?tags=buyer,toronto. The response contains clients that have any of the tags specified.

parameters.name: showSavedSearches
parameters.description: Enables automatic retrieval of Saved Searches for each client in the response. For best performance it's recommended to disable this setting if Saved Searches are not required.

parameters.name: externalId
parameters.description: Filter clients by their identifier from an external system (such as a CRM).

patch.description: Use this endpoint to update a client's information.

agentId.description: The agentId of the agent that this client is assigned to. Each client must be assigned to an agent.

fname.description: The first name of this client

lname.description: The last name of this client.

phone.description:
The mobile phone number of this client (May be used to deliver text messages). Must be 11 digits in length.

Regex pattern: ^(1)([0-9]{10})$

status.description: If false, disables all operations for the client.

email.description: If false, the client will not receive messages via email

sms.description: If false, the client will not receive messages via sms (text)

unsubscribe.description: If true, unsubscribes the client from all forms of communication.

tags.description: You may categorize this client using tags. Tags are useful for filtering purposes and building lists of specific clients. For example, if this client is a buyer from Toronto, you may want to create tags for "Buyer" and "Toronto".

externalId.description: The externalId is intended for storing client identifiers from external systems (such as CRMs) for reference purposes.

delete.description: Use this endpoint to delete a client.

get.description: Use this endpoint to get details about a specific client.
Use this endpoint to get a list of all the tags that you've assigned to clients.

patch.description: Use this endpoint if you'd like to rename a tag. This is useful if you're reorganizing tags and you'd like to combine them with other tags or rename them in a more intuitive way.

parameters.name: tag
parameters.description: The name of the tag that you'd like to rename

label.description: The new name that you'd like to give to the tag.

post.description: Use this endpoint to create a saved search for a client.Important - When a saved search is updated the filters must be specific enough so that the initial matches do not exceed 100 listings otherwise a 406 (not accepted) response will be received.

areas.description: An array of areas to be used as a filter for this search. Required if a value for map is not provided.

basement.description: If specified, matches only listings whose basement description match all of the supplied values. For a list of supported values, make a GET /listings?listings=false&aggregates=details.basement1,details.basement2 request.

cities.description: An array of cities to be used as a filter for this search. Required if a value for map is not provided.

class.description:
Indicates what class of property to search for.

Allowed values:

residential,condo,commercial

clientId.description: The clientId of the client that the search is for. This client will receive notifications from the agent that's assigned to them when listings that match the saved search criteria are listed.

heating.description: An array of heating values to be used as a filter for this search.

name.description: You can specify a name for the saved search. This is useful in cases where users have multiple saved searches, to help them distinguish between saved searches.

neighborhoods.description: An array of neighborhoods to be used as a filter for this search. Required if a value for map is not provided.

notificationFrequency.description:
Sets the frequency that clients will be notified of listings that match their search criteria.

post.description: Use this endpoint to estimate a property's value by providing us with the property's attributes. For more information refer to the AI-Powered Property Estimates Implementation Guide.

extras.description: A comma-separated string that itemizes the home's features. For example, "Hardwood floors throughout, professional landscaping, custom deck, dry sauna, pot lights, smooth ceilings, dual vanity in primary bedroom"

sendEmailNow.description: If set to true and there's a clientId specified, the client will receive a message immediately with a link that will allow them to access their estimate. Note - your account must have the Repliers messaging addon to use this feature.

sendEmailMonthly.description: If set to true and there's a clientId specified, the client will receive a message on a monthly basis with a link to a current estimate.  Note - your account must have the Repliers messaging addon to use this feature.

clientId.description: Set this to the clientId that the estimate is for if you wish to store the estimate. If sendEmailNow or sendEmailMonthly is used, messages containing estimates will be sent to this clientId.

post.description:
Use this endpoint to send a message.

A message is either sent from an agent to a client, or from a client to an agent.

Messages can be used to facilitate communication between agents and their clients for marketing automation or general communication.

Text messaging and email is supported.

agent,client

pictures.description: An array of pictures (URLs) to be sent in this message.
